'''John "Jack" Waring''' is a former professional [[rugby league]] [[footballer]] of the 1940s who at representative level has played for [[England national rugby league team|England]], and at club level for [[St Helens RLFC]].

==International Honours==
Jack Waring won a cap for [[England national rugby league team|England]] while at St. Helens in 1940 against Wales.<ref name="International Statistics at englandrl.co.uk">{{cite web|url=http://www.englandrl.co.uk/international_stats.php?GBSearch=Waring&EnSearch=Waring&submit_x=7&submit_y=3&submit.x=7&submit.y=8|title=International Statistics at englandrl.co.uk|publisher=englandrl|date=2008-12-31|accessdate=2009-01-01}}</ref>

